messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 10/7/2005 8:28:57 PM Central Daylight Time, aisliin@yahoo.com writes: -=-I did send a long post on this topic some time  ago. -=- Some time
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 10/7/2005 8:28:57 PM Central Daylight Time,
aisliin@... writes:

-=-I did send a long post on this topic some time ago. -=-

"Some time ago" is too vague to ring a bell.
If you go to AlwaysLearning's main page, click on mesages, and look in the
days or week you think it was posted and it's not there, it means it never
went through to the list. If you see it there, it means it went at least to
that page. Very occasionally there'll be a yahoo glitch where some people on a
list don't get their mail. It's not often.

Also, sometimes (on lists, at parties, wherever) something is said that's
the last word, or everyone else was busy or distracted and just didn't respond.


Sandra
